data.title: New Releases: May 12, 2023
data.meta_description: New releases and reissues: Jonas Brothers, Moby, Parker McCollum, Overmono, etc.
data.text: Artist: Title: Label: The Acacia Strain “Step Into the Light” (producer: Randy LeBoeuf; guests: Jacob Lilly, Josef Alfonso; new single: “FRESH BONES”; See here; Vinyl; Download; Apple Music; On Tour) » BUY NOW (Rise) Jonas Brothers “The Album” (producer: Jon Bellion; new single: “Wings”; See here; Read here; Target-Exclusive CD, with two bonus tracks; Vinyl; Target-Exclusive Apple Red Vinyl; Download; Apple Music; On Tour; Merch) » BUY NOW (Republic) Parker McCollum “Never Enough” (new single: “I Ain’t Going Nowhere”; Hear here; On Tour) » BUY NOW (MCA Nashville) Madison McFerrin “I Hope You Can Forgive Me” (debut album from the daughter of Bobby McFerrin; guest: Bobby McFerrin; new single: “[Please Don’t] Leave Me Now”; See here; Amazon UK; Download; Apple Music; On Tour) » BUY NOW (MADMCFERRIN MUSIC) Parker Millsap “Wilderness Within You” (new singles: “Running On Time” and “What You’ve Shown Me”; See here; Vinyl; Download; Apple Music; On Tour) » BUY NOW (Okrahoma / Thirty Tigers) Moby “Resound NYC” (15 reimagined tracks he wrote between 1994-2010 while living in New York City; guests: Gregory Porter, Margo Timmins, Damien Jurado, Ricky Wilson, Nicole Scherzinger, Marsha Wallace, Danielle Ponder, Lady Blackbird, Amythyst Kiah, et al; See here; Double Vinyl; Double Crystal Clear Vinyl; Amazon UK; Download; Apple Music) » BUY NOW (Deutsche Grammophon) Overmono “Good Lies” (new single: “Is U”; See here; Apple Music; Vinyl; Download; On Tour) » BUY NOW (XL Recordings) Softee “Natural” (guests: Jordan Webb, Namir Blade; new single: “Come Home”; See here; Apple Music) » BUY NOW (City Slang)
